			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Highsun<a name="68183"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 26 04 2:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mobs have a type of agro consideration called Chase Range.  If you have agro'd a mob in any way (including highsun), it will always chase you if you are within its chase range.  
<br />

<br />
Chase range is mob dependant.  Some will chase you across an entire zone, others wont chase you after a few seconds of distance.  You have to play with this song to see how various mobs will chase you.
<br />

<br />
The song is very very awesome though, many tricks you can do with it.  Even if a mob continues to chase you, you can repeatedly highsun it to keep it away.  
<br />

<br />
Some fun things to do with this song:
<br />

<br />
Gate Vindi repeatedly while force kills his guards, then bring him (save time on silly monk splitting).
<br />
PoE rings, gating the unmezzable, unsnareable, unrootable Red cons (forget which ring it is, Dust I think).
<br />
Kill your group by gating a summoning mob to bind after it is damaged while you fade off agro (only do this once, no one else finds it funny).
<br />

<br />
As Tinu said, Dirge is a true AE spell, in which you and group members are acceptable targets if the center of the AE is cast within range of you.  Party members are immune from damage, but still take up a target.  I believe Dirge hits 4 or 5 targets, so it is best when you have a clump of mobs far away from you, your group, and anything you don't want to agro.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
