				<td colspan="2"><span>I will definitely usethis next time. I was in KC the other night and had just done a camp check, when a mage brings a mini-train to me. Well, not really a problem, I was set up for kite mode, but could take a few of these guys. 
<br />

<br />
Once done with that I again do a camp check. Silence.
<br />

<br />
Then I'm just hanging in tell h*ll with some friends and notice the Mage bringing more fun to me. 
<br />

<br />
Well I take the time to charm one and DoT and slash the others. No Problemo.
<br />

<br />
Now a Ranger comes into the zone and Mageboy has brought another group of fun ones to me. So now I have mez and tanking song lineup ready to go. I mez two and take on the other 3. No Problem, right? The Ranger breaks one mez, then the next and says &quot;Whoops, sorry Bro&quot;
<br />

<br />
I reapply mez and bring the fun to another side of zone in. He proceeds to break the mez again and again. So I finally get down to the last two, but by now have taken enough damage that I really don't want to run nekked back to KC, so I zone.
<br />

<br />
I come back in and he and his Mage friend have set up camp and are doing there thing. 
<br />

<br />
Now I have not even attempted to pull anything at this point. I was just standing at zone in /oocing camp check, right?
<br />

<br />
Well I see the two of them turn at me and get ready to bring another train. 
<br />

<br />
So I set up charm shop. Grab the a Drolvarg and send him all the way past these clowns to a spectral beasty at the end of the hall. Aggroing everything en route and get a nice handful of fun fun mobs. 
<br />

<br />
I then mem the fear tune, break charm. They all come a running back to me. I fear them and give 'em that nice little speed boost. They run haywire throughout the zone and grab a bunch more friends. Well the train I see coming back is HUGE. It looks like one big mass of graphics. I wait until they reach the friendly trainers/mez breakers then fade. Whoopsie!
<br />

<br />
Happy Birthday!
<br />

<br />
See? There is a wicked side to everyone. I have helped more folks than can count and often help strangers, but lesson being, don't mess with a Bard. We always get the last laugh!
<br />

<br />
Should there be a next time, I'll DA run through at Selo's, Deftdance, bring back the fun, then Fade. Let's not forget the popcorn.
<br />

