				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: ~<a name="68515"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 29 04 10:40 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I was never a huge fan of highsun until I got FM. With such a short range it always just seemed easier to mez or charm. After FM though, it has definite applications. I still generally prefer to mez-fade split, but where you are dealing with unmezzable mobs (like Vindi) or even worse unmezzable, unsnareable mobs (DAs in UP spring to mind) then highsun-fade splitting definitely starts looking attractive.
<br />

<br />
Kazumi is an excellent song that I keep up most of the time. However if I feel that I might use it in an emergency on the group I let them know in advance what they are to do. I also collaborate with my cleric partner - typically she will heal over time just before kazumi lands.
<br />

<br />
However the main thing I use kazumi for these days is when pulling. With all the snaring mobs in GoD and OoW it is the perfect tool for bringing in those long pulls with minimal damage. Again, it helps alot that I can communicate verbally with my partner to say when I can be healed safely.
<br />

<br />
